 assets into a winddown vehicle to ensure their continued safe operation until they can be sold the companys international subsidiaries will not be included as part of the chapter  cases but will be part of the sale process what is the amount really owed to the lenders it is now important to read the k filing and stay away from any interpretation from the press release which is quite misleading in my opinion the k filing is saying the following pursuant to the ar forbearance agreement the borrower received written notice from the agent that the commitments under the first lien credit agreement are terminated and the outstanding loans under the first lien credit agreement are declared due and payable in whole including without limitation the principal of the loans under the first lien credit agreement together with accrued interest thereon unpaid accrued fees the applicable premium as defined in the first lien credit agreement and all other obligations of the borrower accrued under the first lien credit agreement and any other loan document as defined under the first lien credit agreement what does it mean assuming that the plan will be approved and prior to the distribution hercules offshore owes at least  million plus unpaid and accrued interest to the first lien lenders from the  million here is an excerpt of the credit agreement in the k page  term sheet as of the rsa effective date the aggregate amount of first lien claims is  million plus accrued and unpaid interest prior to taking into account any prepayments thereon contemplated by the amended and restated forbearance agreement however if the plan is approved if the class of holders of hero common stock votes to accept the plan the first lien lenders shall receive their pro rata share of nysei a noninterest bearing senior claim against the wind down entity in the amount of usd  million less the escrow release payment as defined in the term sheet and any amounts previously distributed to the first lien lenders during the chapter  cases and ii  of class a interests in the wind down entity which shall represent  of the acceptance wind down entity interests as defined in the term sheet the distribution will be  to the shareholders the wsj article said tuesday as hercules pushed crucial early motions through court centerbridge lawyer andrew glenn accused senior lenders of manufacturing an unnecessary bankruptcy to collect a premium for early payoff of their debt why are we here today given that the company has well over  million in cash… and oil has rebounded mr glenn asked centerbridge partners lp is a private investment firm with offices in new york and london the firm focuses on private equity  credit investments centerbridge partners owns  shares of hero as of  per hercules offshore website the lawyer for centerbridge partners m andrew glenn accused the senior lenders to have created a situation to collect an applicable premium  roughly  million  which i think is an issue that can be potentially debated if the right argument is used and if the issue of the initial default is questioned however what i do not understand is that m andrew glenn indicated that this situation is unnecessary due in part because the oil has rebounded which is certainly the wrong argument in my opinion this explanation lacks of offshore drilling knowledge unfortunately yes it is true that oil has experienced a strong positive momentum and now trades above  per barrel i would say so what nevertheless it is not true that the offshore drillers have enjoyed any positive effects from this oil rally and in fact the basic market situation is getting much worse since early march the offshore drilling industry shallow and deep water as well has not improved and the tendering activity has totally vanished beside some rare contract extensions negotiated at a dismal day rate it is a fact that no one can refute on the other side m dublin lawyer for hercules offshore talked about unsuccessful sale process to explain why hero needs to return to chapter  i would argue that the company has been extremely slow and notoriously inefficient in this sale process shareholders would like to see what has been done in this domain since emerging from the first bankruptcy can we use procrastination the second argument about the potential cash burn rate is more convincing and quite appealing i estimated a cash burn rate of approximately  million per quarter which is pretty close to the amount advanced by m dublin  million at the end of  nevertheless m andrew glenn said that shareholders were expecting this loss of cash in  and were holding on for a return to profitability in  to support this thinking he said recent forecasts put out by the company show hercules will be back in the black next year however shareholders that will be pushed out if the companys new bankruptcy scenario plays out wont be around to enjoy those profits and neither will hercules hercules plans to shut down its business and sell off assets in chapter  with some of the proceeds going to shareholders if they support its plan and concluded that hercules offshore doesnt belong to a bankruptcy court and estimated that the lenders are orchestrating the liquidation of this company mr glenn said noting that hercules is in chapter  not because of unrelenting gloom in the oil industry but because lenders want to cash in even if it kills the company i have to agree with centerbridge partners on this subject and said that the lenders were not confident enough to let hercules offshore getting its hands on the  million in escrow for the hercules highlander thereby used the first pretext to claim a breach federal bankruptcy watchdogs are weighing the appointment of an official committee of equity stakeholders in herculess chapter  case centerbridge is urging that a shareholder panel be named hercules said a shareholder committee could cause delay that risks plunging the company into a freefall bankruptcy in a freefall hercules would be forced into fast sales of its assets rather than the controlled sales that the company thinks will bring the best value the judge however seemed inclined to let shareholders weigh in on the question of herculess future i am concerned that the interests of equity be fully represented judge kevin carey said at tuesdays hearing in the us bankruptcy court in wilmington del he rejected urging from hercules to set a july  date to confirm its chapter  plan which is being circulated for shareholder votes now centerbridge is urging that the confirmation hearing be pushed off to give an equity committee time to investigate and take a stand on herculess future m dublin heros lawyer said the following efforts to find a buyer that would take over the operating company drew only non cash bids in amounts insufficient to cover the debt he added as we know hercules offshore handed the hercules highlander over to a subsidiary of maersk drilling getting out from under an obligation to pay  million to complete the rig lenders reclaimed the  million escrowed funds on a final note m glenn said that the sale of the hercules highlander will be a major focus this part is quite strange because i do not think hero has anything to do with the rig and has nothing to sale it would be really important that the company takes the time to explain in detail the status of the hercules highlander and if the company can claim any cash which i doubt conclusion i do not see this situation as a positive event for common shareholders if centerbridge is successful in his attempt hercules offshore will be forced to sell assets quickly and at an extremely distressed level that may or may not cover the debt and leave shareholders with a perfect zero on the other hand this second bankruptcy will allow time to sell the assets at higher price and eventually gives a potential cash distribution for the common shareholders i do not think it will be high but it will be better than zero at least again as i said in my preceding article do not count your chickens before they hatched i recommend to stay away for hero now because it is too risky disclosure iwe have no positions in any stocks mentioned and no plans to initiate any positions within the next  hours i wrote this article myself and it expresses my own opinions i am not receiving compensation for it other than from seeking alpha i have no business relationship with any company whose stock is mentioned in this article editors note this article covers one or more stocks trading at less than  per share andor with less than a  million market cap please be aware of the risks associated with these stocksabout this articleexpandauthor payment   page view authors of pro articles receive a minimum guaranteed payment of tagged basic materials oil  gas drilling  explorationwant to share your opinion on this article add a commentdisagree with this article submit your ownto report a factual error in this article click herefollow fun trading and get email alerts basic materials and energy stocks  seeking alphasign in  join nowgo»basic materials and energy stockstotal sa  q  results  earnings call slidestot• today  pm • sa transcriptstaseko mines new prosperity remains a long shottgb• today  pm • elephant analytics• commentsgoldcorp inc  q  results  earnings call slidesgg• today  pm • sa transcriptscameco corporation  q  results  earnings call slidesccj• today  pm • sa transcripts• commentteck resources limited  q  results  earnings call slidesteck• today  pm • sa transcriptsschlumberger stay cautiousslb• today  pm • sarfaraz a khananadarko petroleum could have a cash flow problemapc• today  pm • sarfaraz a khanarcelormittal  q  results  earnings call slidesmt• today  pm • sa transcriptsis american midstream a good longterm investmentamid• today  pm • orthodox investor• commentsbp trying to make the best out of a bad situationbp• today  pm • sarfaraz a khan• commentssuncoke energy  q  results  earnings call slidessxc• today  pm 